data.enText: a thing or an event that exists or comes before another, and may have influenced it
the people in sb's family who lived a long time ago
a word or phrase to which the following word, especially a pronoun, refers

data.chText: 在He grabbed the ball and threw it in the air一句中，ball是it的先行词。
data.enText: In ‘He grabbed the ball and threw it in the air’, ‘ball’ is the antecedent of ‘it’.

simple_means.memory_skill: ante 前面 + ced 行走，前进 + ent 具有…性质的 → 先行的；以前的

tr: a phrase or clause that is referred to by an anaphoric pronoun
a preceding occurrence or cause or event
someone from whom you are descended (but usually more remote than a grandparent)
anything that precedes something similar in time
example: phrenology was an antecedent of modern neuroscience

value.def: An antecedent of something happened or existed before it and was similar to it in some way.

example.ex: We shall first look briefly at the historical antecedents of this theory.
example.tran: 我们首先应大致看一下该理论在历史上的前身。

value.def: An antecedent thing or event happened or existed before another related thing or event.

example.ex: It was permissible to take account of antecedent legislation.

example.tran: 祖先为爱尔兰人的法国人

rootsaffixes.title: ced, ceed, cess

pro 向前 + cess 行走，前进 → 向前走的〔历程〕→ 过程
